sp.p:
What ſay you, Brothers, I think his Requeſt is very reaſonable,
he appears not to be in a condition of taking his Tryal now;
And Mr. Attorney is willing he ſhould be ſet aſide till next Seſſions.

I am not, nor no man is to be Tryed upon a preſumption;
'tis but a conceit in Law, and penal Laws are to be taken
ſtrictly in favour of the Priſoner.

Let him name the day, then we could diſprove him;
and let him name the day, and if I do not diſprove him, I will be
hang'd.

Several times in that Summer before the Plot was diſcovered;
and ſeveral times the Winter before, when I came over
from Spain.
